.TH AGA 1 "June 2026" "aga 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
aga \- Attack Graph Analysis: a security toolkit for weighted directed networks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aga
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ CONFIG ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBaga\fR models any network \(em an IT attack graph, a road system, a supply
chain, a social/influence graph \(em as a directed weighted graph and reasons
about its security and robustness using graph theory:
.PP
.IP \(bu 3
CVSS v3.1 Exploitability-derived edge weights, so every weight is traceable to
a public security standard;
.IP \(bu 3
a from-scratch Bellman-Ford shortest-path implementation (with negative-cycle
detection);
.IP \(bu 3
Menger's Theorem machinery (maximum vertex-disjoint paths and minimum vertex
cut, solved three independent ways) to find the smallest set of nodes to defend;
.IP \(bu 3
a composite security score (0\-100) with a letter grade (A\-F);
.IP \(bu 3
vulnerability hotspot detection that flags single points of failure.
.PP
The default behaviour analyses the bundled campus-network preset. Graphs are
plain JSON config files (see
.BR FILES ).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the \fBaga\fR version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a short usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-dir " DIRECTORY"
Analyse every \fB*.json\fR graph config in \fIDIRECTORY\fR and print a
side-by-side comparison table.
.TP
.BI \-\-graphs-dir " DIRECTORY"
Directory of preset graph configs (default: \fB./graphs\fR, or the bundled
presets when the directory is absent).
.TP
.B \-\-list
List available graph presets in the graphs directory and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-no-plot
Skip generating and saving the graph visualisation (headless / CI mode).
.TP
.BI \-\-explain-cvss " VECTOR"
Explain, step by step, how a CVSS vector (e.g.
.BR "AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N" )
becomes an edge weight, then exit. No graph is analysed.
.TP
.B \-\-list-templates
List the built-in graph-construction templates and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-construct " TEMPLATE"
Construct a graph from a named template (zero access) and analyse it.
.TP
.BI \-\-discover " FILE"
Construct a graph from a discovery JSON file (describing what was observed vs
inferred, with an access level) and analyse it.
.TP
.BI \-\-wifi-from-file " FILE"
Construct a WiFi attack graph from a captured \fBnmcli\fR scan output file
(offline; for demos/testing) and analyse it.
.TP
.BI \-\-scan-wifi " [\fIIFACE\fR]"
Run a LIVE passive WiFi scan on \fIIFACE\fR (or auto-detect), construct the
attack graph, and analyse it. Requires
.BR \-\-i-am-authorized .
Only scan networks you own or are authorised to assess.
.TP
.B \-\-i-am-authorized
Authorisation gate for \fB\-\-scan-wifi\fR and \fB\-\-nmap-live\fR. By passing
this flag you assert you are authorised to scan the target/airspace.
.TP
.B \-\-wifi-rescan
With \fB\-\-scan-wifi\fR, trigger a fresh \fBnmcli\fR rescan first.
.TP
.BI \-\-nmap " FILE"
Construct an attack graph from an nmap XML output file (\fBnmap \-oX\fR), the
network INTERIOR layer. Offline and safe.
.TP
.BI \-\-nmap-live " TARGET"
Run nmap LIVE against \fITARGET\fR (e.g.
.BR 10.0.0.0/24 ),
build the graph, and analyse it. Sends packets \(em requires
.BR \-\-i-am-authorized .
.TP
.BI \-\-export " PATH"
Also export the analysed graph to \fIPATH\fR. The format is chosen from the
extension: \fB.graphml\fR/\fB.xml\fR (GraphML), \fB.dot\fR/\fB.gv\fR (Graphviz
DOT), \fB.json\fR (round-trip config).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Analyse the default (bundled) preset:
.B aga
.TP
Analyse a specific graph, headless:
.B aga graphs/campus_cvss.json \-\-no-plot
.TP
Compare every graph in a directory:
.B aga \-\-dir graphs/
.TP
Explain a CVSS vector:
.B aga \-\-explain-cvss "AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N"
.TP
Build a graph from nmap output and export it:
.B aga \-\-nmap scan.xml \-\-export out.graphml
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The base install is headless (depends only on networkx). Graph rendering needs
matplotlib, installed via the \fBplot\fR extra
(\fBpip install attack-graph-analysis[plot]\fR) or the Debian package's
\fBpython3-matplotlib\fR recommendation.
.SH FILES
Graph configs are JSON. An edge may be written in three forms: an explicit
weight \fI{"from","to","weight"}\fR, a compact triple \fI[u, v, w]\fR, or a
CVSS-derived form \fI{"from","to","cvss"}\fR (the weight is computed at load
time). Weights must be positive.
.SH NOTES
WiFi and nmap live scanning are passive/active respectively and are gated by
\fB\-\-i-am-authorized\fR. This tool performs NO exploitation: no
deauthentication, handshake capture, packet injection, or key cracking.
